OL,4,CSri Lanka adoption: The babies who were
OL,5,Cgiven away
OL,6, Thousands of Sri Lankan babies were put
OL,7, up for adoption between the 1960s and
OL,8, 1980s - some of them sold by "baby
OL,9, farms" to prospective parents across
OL,10, Europe. The Netherlands, which accepted
OL,11, many of those infants, has recently
OL,12, suspended international adoptions
OL,13, following historical allegations of
OL,14, coercion and bribery. As that
OL,15, investigation unfolds, families who
OL,16, never stopped thinking about the
OL,17, children who vanished hope they will be
OL,18, reunited.
